00:40:49.300 --> 00:40:55.379
in one way, I try and take the company out of this equation. Totally, you know, not just our

00:40:55.379 --> 00:41:00.580
immediate needs. And I think, okay, what's going to be really great for this person's career

00:41:00.580 --> 00:41:06.659
in general? Like if I bump into you five years or 10 years down the line, in a selfish way,

00:41:06.659 --> 00:41:11.780
it would be fantastic if your career was just going swimmingly, right? It's good to have

00:41:12.659 --> 00:41:19.300
contacts whose careers are just really flying. And then I sort of work backwards from that.

00:41:19.300 --> 00:41:24.020
And I say, okay, you know, I think, you know, would this be better for you? Would that be better

00:41:24.020 --> 00:41:29.300
for you? Or, you know, don't worry too much. Like if you could do anything, what would you do?

00:41:29.300 --> 00:41:33.860
